<dl id="n53100d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53100d">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53100d"> 100(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Mennonites</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The <mark>Mennonites</mark> were members of a religious sect. They took their name from Menno Simons (1492-1559), an Anabaptist, who refused to take an oath, to bear arms, or to occupy civic or State offices. The Mennonites fled to Holland and Moravia, thence to Russia, and from there to America.] <small> Athelstan Ridgway, ed. <a name="RDOD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RDOD"><cite title="source">A Dictionary of Dates</cite></a> (1932) M</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
